        <h2 class="featurette-heading">The Girls</h2>
        <p class="lead">We try to pick girls that have demonstrated need, motivation and potential for success.</p>
        <p>The sad fact is that we can’t help every rural girl in Zambia; we don’t have the resources. This makes it especially important to maximize the effect we can have. We do this through selecting the most promising girls.</p>
        <p>The process starts with a foreign development worker on the ground in Zambia identifying a girl. We use currently serving development workers because they have experienced the girl’s situation first hand and are the most qualified to make a decisions in the proper context. We use foreign workers because they are not bound by the clan, familial or tribal ties of the area. We want girls who deserve our help based on their merit, not their connections.</p>
        <p>If the girl is interested in applying, then she and the development worker will complete the application together and send it to Insaka. We will collect the applications, choose the best ones, and put their profiles up on our website.</p>
        <p>We will provide updates on the girls' progress as we can. </p>
    </div>
    
